New Delhi: President Uhuru Kenyatta was formally received in India by President Pranab Mukherjee and Prime Minister Narendra Modi.The State reception was at the official residence of the Indian President in New Delhi, where President Uhuru was accorded a 21-gun salute. President Kenyatta, who is on a reciprocal State visit to India, was escorted into the official residence of the Indian President by mounted troops shortly after 10:00 am (Indian time).The firing of 21 cannons at the ceremony traditionally reserved for Heads of State and Government was followed by the national anthems of Kenya and India played by the Indian military band.Thereafter, President Kenyatta inspected a guard of honour mounted by a detachment of the Indian military. ALSO READ: DP Ruto asks Rift Valley leaders to back Uhuru with eye on 2022Addressing the press after the ceremonies, President Kenyatta said the reciprocal visit would further strengthen the cordial relations between Kenya and India. He said the visit would also boost the economic, cultural and social ties that the two countries have always enjoyed.Later, the Head of State visited Raj Ghat (the Mahatma Gandhi Memorial) where he laid a wreath in remembrance of the legendary leader of the Indian independence struggle who inspired movements for civil rights and freedom across the world.